Ruth Bosibori Nyangau (nke a na-akpọkwa Ruth Bisibori; amụrụ na ọnwa Jenụwarị 2, na afọ 1988 na Bosiango) bụ onye Kenya na-agba ọsọ n'etiti etiti nke bụ ọkachamara na 3000 mita steeplechase.
N'ọnwa Julaị afọ 2007 ọ ghọrọ onye mmeri mbụ nke All-Africa Games na ihe omume ahụ, dịka emere ya na nke mbụ ya
N'ọnwa Ọgọstụ n'otu afọ ahụ, ọ mechara nke anọ na World Championships na oge ndekọ ụwa nke 9:25.25 nkeji
Ihe ndekọ ochie ahụ bụ 9:30.70 ma bụrụ nke Melissa Rollison. Na afo 2008 African Championships in Athletics ọ mechara nke atọ.

A mụrụ Bosibori n'obodo Bosiango dị nso na Kisii. 
Ọ malitere ịgba ọsọ na afọ 2003 mgbe ọ nọ na Kebirichi Secondary School
Ndị uwe ojii Kenya kpọrọ ya mgbe ọ meriri asọmpi mpaghara n'afọ 2007. A na-eji ya eme asọmpi ụkwụ ọtọ.

O meriri na Most Promising Sportswoman of the Year category na afọ 2007 Kenyan Sports Personality of the Year awards. Dan Muchoki zụrụ ya ruo n'afọ 2007, mgbe onye nkuzi Ịtali Renato Canova malitere iso ya, mgbe ọ gara n'okpuru nlekọta Gianni Demadonna.
N'afọ 2009, ọ meziwanyere ihe kachasị mma ya ruo 9:13.16, na-emeri na 2009 IAAF World Athletics Final site na sekọnd asaa.
N'afọ 2010, ọ mụrụ nwa ya nwanyị Glory (na Septemba)
Ọ chọrọ ịlaghachi na ngwụcha afọ 2011, na-ele anya na Olympic Games na afọ 2012 na London.
